    {
      "title": "Project Update: June 24, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Development on June 24, 2026 centered on two main areas: finalizing streaming documentation and addressing critical cloud infrastructure security concerns. On the completed side, the team wrapped up documentation for token-by-token dashboard streaming, including in-browser video evidence verifying the functionality against Together AI cloud models. On the infrastructure front, two pull requests are currently in progress targeting cloud security and networking. One PR aims to isolate untrusted app builds from the runtime fleet and has been flagged as a high-priority Product-2 blocker requiring immediate review. A second PR addresses network configuration by binding app host ports to loopback and routing through a node-local Caddy instance for app ingress. These open items represent critical blockers that must be resolved to ensure a secure cloud deployment.",
